.\}
Get the current log from the device and dumps it to stdout:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
# nvme toshiba vs\-smart\-add\-log /dev/nvme0
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Get the contents of log page 0xC0 from the device and save to a binary file:
.sp
